 total. Dust lane identification does not depend on disk ellipticity (disk\nthickness) or Sersic profile but correlates with bulge morphology; a round\nbulge favors dust lane votes.\n  The central component along the line of sight that produces the dust lane is\nnot associated with either one of the components fit by {\\sc magphys}, the cold\ndiffuse component or the localized, heated component in HII regions, but a mix\nof these two.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 16 Sep 2019 20:11:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
